Tyronne Ebuehi has expressed delight after signing a five-year contract with Portuguese side Benfica. Ebuehi who made the Super Eagles provisional squad to the 2018 World Cup in Russia said it was hard to resist the chance to join Benfica who have been scouting him. May 19, 2018 In "Sports" Norwich City look to have lost out to Portuguese giants Benfica in the race to sign Super Eagles right-back Tyronne Ebuehi. January 16, 2018 In "News" Super Eagles may be without Tyronne Ebuehi for their international friendly against Ukraine after the young defender picked up an injury during a training with his club Benfica last week. August 20, 2019 In "News"